  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 83,
    "rationale": "Strong, low-dispersion house agreement: 7 of the 8 members who express a market posture are risk_on at high conviction (80\u201388) \u2014 citing regulatory clarity (GENIUS passed, CLARITY advancing), >$1T monthly stablecoin volume, institutions making real commitments, and maturing infrastructure. The two non-aligned members are not bearish: Thaler is structurally optimistic but a neutral deployer (research lead), and Roughgarden expresses no market view (academic). The bullishness is selective and substance-based, not indiscriminate \u2014 the same members actively warn against speculative/extractive categories (memecoins, disguised-equity tokens, DATs) and against unfinished market-structure legislation. Conviction trimmed modestly from the ~85 risk_on mean to reflect those two abstaining/neutral voices and the execution-level caveats.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Consensus weights both conviction and coverage: items held strongly by many members (stablecoins, defi, ai-crypto, institutional-adoption, ETH) dominate, while lone or low-conviction views are faded (e.g., USDT/EIGEN/WLD bullish, TRUMP bearish, enterprise-gtm-weakness) and kept only at reduced conviction where non-contradicted. High-conviction-but-narrow research specialties (network-tokens 94.5, zkvm 96) are included but coverage-discounted because they reflect 1\u20132 builder-researchers rather than a broad allocation stance. THREE items are genuinely SPLIT and reflected as such with deliberately lowered/neutral conviction: (1) crypto-policy-regulation (stance_dispersion 0.94) \u2014 rendered neutral; the real shared signal is 'finish market-structure legislation,' not directional bearishness; (2) BTC (stance_dispersion 1.0, mean sign 0) \u2014 rendered neutral, bullish-as-commodity vs. bearish-on-quantum on non-contradicting axes; (3) prover-performance (stance_dispersion 1.0) \u2014 omitted from the lists as an internal research-progress debate (concern easing over time) rather than a market view. The clear through-line connecting the house's top theses is money-and-AI moving onchain: stablecoins + agentic/micropayments as the rails, DeFi/RWA/institutional adoption as the demand, and privacy + proof-of-personhood + verifiable compute (zk/network-token economics) as the enabling trust layer. No items were invented; names reuse members' exact item strings. Token-level conviction is generally lower than sector-level because most members speak in sectors/frameworks and several token mentions are infrastructure/legal-classification signals rather than price calls."
}